{
  "text": "When we first introduced CRsAE [CITATION_1] , it was as an interpretable deep residual AE architecture for CDL. Here, we leverage the connection between CDL and EM to further extend the architecture in such a way that both H and \u03bb can be learned. In the new formulation of CRsAE, the forward pass of the architecture plays the role of E-step giving an estimate of the sparse code x, and in the training stage, the backward pass updates the filters H and regularization parameter \u03bb through a two-stage back-propagation.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "49670566"
